text.section:
For the following counties and municipal corporations the rate of interest for each month or fraction of a month that county or municipal corporation property tax or taxing district property tax is overdue is:
1% for Garrett County;
1% for the City of Salisbury;
1% for Washington County;
1% for Somerset County; and
the rate set by law by:
the governing body of a county that has adopted a charter form of government under Article XI-A of the Maryland Constitution;
the governing body of:
the Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City for Baltimore City, if the rate is set on or before June 30 for the following taxable year.
